-- Toyota on track for 5-7 pct U.S. sales rise
-- 
-- Tue Oct 2, 2007 4:00pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/10/02/us-toyota-forecast-idUSN0242726820071002

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - Toyota Motor Corp ( 7203.T ) on Tuesday said it is confident of achieving its sales growth target of 5 percent to 7 percent for the U.S. market in 2007. 

 "We are confident the next few months will keep us on track to achieve our growth targets for the rest of the year," Toyota spokesman Irv Miller said on a conference call with analysts and reporters. Miller also said the Japanese automaker, which posted a 0.6 percent drop in September sales on an adjusted basis, is on track to sell 200,000 Tundra pickup trucks this year.